          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are often used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to validate exchange codes, which are typically used in financial or telecommunications contexts to identify specific exchanges or markets."
